# Power Query Transformation Guide

## Folder Connection Pattern

1. Open Power BI Desktop.
2. Select `Get Data` > `Text/CSV`.
3. Load each CSV from the `Dataset` folder.
4. Use `Transform Data` before loading into the model.
5. Apply the data type map from `Dataset/data_dictionary.md`.

## Transformation Standards

- Promote first row as headers.
- Trim and clean text columns.
- Set fact numeric fields to fixed decimal or whole number.
- Set date fields to Date type.
- Replace blank categorical values with `Unknown`.
- Remove duplicate dimension rows by natural/business key.
- Keep surrogate keys as whole numbers.

## Example M Query: FactSales

```powerquery
let
    ProjectRoot = "C:\Users\ironside\Downloads\New folder (2)\Retail-Enterprise-Analytics",
    Source = Csv.Document(
        File.Contents(ProjectRoot & "\Dataset\FactSales.csv"),
        [Delimiter=",", Encoding=65001, QuoteStyle=QuoteStyle.Csv]
    ),
    PromotedHeaders = Table.PromoteHeaders(Source, [PromoteAllScalars=true]),
    ChangedType = Table.TransformColumnTypes(
        PromotedHeaders,
        {
            {"SalesKey", Int64.Type},
            {"OrderID", type text},
            {"DateKey", Int64.Type},
            {"CustomerKey", Int64.Type},
            {"ProductKey", Int64.Type},
            {"StoreKey", Int64.Type},
            {"RegionKey", Int64.Type},
            {"Quantity", Int64.Type},
            {"UnitPrice", Currency.Type},
            {"DiscountAmount", Currency.Type},
            {"SalesAmount", Currency.Type},
            {"CostAmount", Currency.Type},
            {"ProfitAmount", Currency.Type},
            {"PaymentMethod", type text},
            {"OrderChannel", type text},
            {"FulfillmentStatus", type text}
        }
    ),
    TrimmedText = Table.TransformColumns(
        ChangedType,
        {
            {"OrderID", Text.Trim, type text},
            {"PaymentMethod", Text.Trim, type text},
            {"OrderChannel", Text.Trim, type text},
            {"FulfillmentStatus", Text.Trim, type text}
        }
    ),
    RemovedDuplicates = Table.Distinct(TrimmedText, {"SalesKey"}),
    ValidatedAmounts = Table.AddColumn(
        RemovedDuplicates,
        "AmountValidationStatus",
        each if Number.Abs(([Quantity] * [UnitPrice] - [DiscountAmount]) - [SalesAmount]) <= 0.01
             and Number.Abs(([SalesAmount] - [CostAmount]) - [ProfitAmount]) <= 0.01
             then "Valid"
             else "Review",
        type text
    )
in
    ValidatedAmounts
```

## Example M Query: Dimension De-Duplication

```powerquery
let
    ProjectRoot = "C:\Users\ironside\Downloads\New folder (2)\Retail-Enterprise-Analytics",
    Source = Csv.Document(
        File.Contents(ProjectRoot & "\Dataset\DimProduct.csv"),
        [Delimiter=",", Encoding=65001, QuoteStyle=QuoteStyle.Csv]
    ),
    PromotedHeaders = Table.PromoteHeaders(Source, [PromoteAllScalars=true]),
    ChangedType = Table.TransformColumnTypes(
        PromotedHeaders,
        {
            {"ProductKey", Int64.Type},
            {"SKU", type text},
            {"ProductName", type text},
            {"Category", type text},
            {"Subcategory", type text},
            {"Brand", type text},
            {"UnitCost", Currency.Type},
            {"ListPrice", Currency.Type},
            {"LaunchDate", type date},
            {"DiscontinuedFlag", Int64.Type}
        }
    ),
    CleanedText = Table.TransformColumns(
        ChangedType,
        {
            {"SKU", each Text.Upper(Text.Trim(_)), type text},
            {"ProductName", each Text.Proper(Text.Trim(_)), type text},
            {"Category", each Text.Proper(Text.Trim(_)), type text},
            {"Subcategory", each Text.Proper(Text.Trim(_)), type text},
            {"Brand", each Text.Trim(_), type text}
        }
    ),
    RemovedDuplicateSku = Table.Distinct(CleanedText, {"SKU"}),
    AddedMarginBand = Table.AddColumn(
        RemovedDuplicateSku,
        "StandardMarginBand",
        each if ([ListPrice] - [UnitCost]) / [ListPrice] >= 0.40 then "High"
             else if ([ListPrice] - [UnitCost]) / [ListPrice] >= 0.25 then "Medium"
             else "Low",
        type text
    )
in
    AddedMarginBand
```

## Recommended Query Groups

- `Staging`: raw CSV imports with type changes.
- `Dimensions`: business-clean dimensions loaded to the model.
- `Facts`: cleansed fact tables loaded to the model.
- `Data Quality`: validation queries disabled for report load but visible to developers.
